    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Guns, Here and There</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jim Chamberlain letter responds to Oct 25 news article on Israeli citizens' enrollment in firearms training; asserts US citizens must never have right to buy guns taken away from them (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In an unpredictable world of change and conflict, many Israeli citizens, seeking the means and skill to defend themselves, are buying guns and taking shooting lessons (''Gun Lessons Are Suddenly All the Rage in Israel,'' news article, Oct. 25).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In an unpredictable world of change and conflict, many Israeli citizens, seeking the means and skill to defend themselves, are buying guns and taking shooting lessons (''Gun Lessons Are Suddenly All the Rage in Israel,'' news article, Oct. 25).</p>
        <p>In an unpredictable world of change and conflict, American citizens must not have their right to do the same taken away from them.</p>
        <p>JIM CHAMBERLAIN  Shorewood, Wis., Oct. 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
